Divide by `Money` or `Number` and return `Tuple` containing
quotient and modulus.

```
Money.new(100).divmod(9)            # => {Money(@amount=0.11), Money(@amount=0.01)}
Money.new(100).divmod(Money.new(9)) # => {11, Money(@amount=0.01)}
```

